Function fold-by-key: (-> Atom Atom Variable Variable Atom Atom %Undefined%) HE-extended grouped fold over nondeterministic results. Evaluates a result fan-out, skips Empty results, computes one grouping key per surviving item, and folds each group into its own accumulator without first packaging the full result set by key in user code. The primary form is (fold-by-key results init $acc $item key step). The policy form (fold-by-key (search-policy lane) results init $acc $item key step) keeps the same lane and ordering controls as select, collect, and fold. The key expression must produce exactly one non-empty key per item. The step expression must produce exactly one non-empty next accumulator. Results are emitted as two-element expressions (key accumulator) in first-encounter order under the active traversal policy.
Parameters:
  Atom Result expression to evaluate
  Atom Initial accumulator value for each key
  Variable Accumulator binder
  Variable Current item binder
  Atom Key expression that yields the grouping key for the current item
  Atom Step expression that yields the next accumulator for the current item's key
Return: (type %Undefined%) Grouped fold results as two-element expressions of key and final accumulator
[(@doc-formal (@item fold-by-key) (@kind function) (@type (-> Atom Atom Variable Variable Atom Atom %Undefined%)) (@desc "HE-extended grouped fold over nondeterministic results. Evaluates a result fan-out, skips Empty results, computes one grouping key per surviving item, and folds each group into its own accumulator without first packaging the full result set by key in user code. The primary form is (fold-by-key results init $acc $item key step). The policy form (fold-by-key (search-policy lane) results init $acc $item key step) keeps the same lane and ordering controls as select, collect, and fold. The key expression must produce exactly one non-empty key per item. The step expression must produce exactly one non-empty next accumulator. Results are emitted as two-element expressions (key accumulator) in first-encounter order under the active traversal policy.") (@params ((@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Result expression to evaluate")) (@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Initial accumulator value for each key")) (@param (@type Variable) (@desc "Accumulator binder")) (@param (@type Variable) (@desc "Current item binder")) (@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Key expression that yields the grouping key for the current item")) (@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Step expression that yields the next accumulator for the current item's key")))) (@return (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Grouped fold results as two-element expressions of key and final accumulator")))]
